Walmart supporters are pleased to note that the protests took place in just nine states and did not cause the corporation the slightest damage.
&quot;Black Friday&quot; continued at its stores from 8 p.m. Thursday until midnight the next day, during which time Walmart was selling about 5,000 items per second.
